define({"topics":[{"title":"Minimum viable docset","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Minimum viable documentation set (MVD) is the smallest amount of documentation needed so that the majority of developers willingly adopt an API, just enough that they don't feel overwhelmed by frustration or give up because the API wastes their time.<\/p>","href":"topics\/minimum-viable-docset_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis-d248e119","topics":[]},{"title":"API reference","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The largest and most important part of the reference documentation is the section that describes all of the API endpoints.<\/p>","href":"topics\/basic-reference_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete-d248e128","topics":[]},{"title":"API reference example","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The following is a reference entry for one endpoint on a fictional API. This is just one way to represent all the necessary information.<\/p>","href":"topics\/reference-example-container_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"example-reference-entry"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"example-reference-entry-d248e137","topics":[]},{"title":"Working with OAS3 and Swagger","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">It's easy to assume that the OAS3 spec endows the documentation with more accuracy or completeness, compared to documentation that is not programmatically generated. Not necessarily. Generating docs from an OAS3 spec can have <em class=\"ph i\">many<\/em> benefits, but it doesn't improve accuracy or completeness because the spec is ultimately written by humans, and information can be missing or incorrect.<\/p>","href":"topics\/swagger-reference_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"whats-missing-from-your-swagger-docs-how-to-ensure-completeness-when-working-with-openapi-3"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"whats-missing-from-your-swagger-docs-how-to-ensure-completeness-when-working-with-openapi-3-d248e146","topics":[]},{"title":"Writing the overview","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you are the first technical writer on a project or if the project is brand new, it most likely lacks an overview. You should write one.<\/p>","href":"topics\/non-reference-overview_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"non-reference-documentation-writing-the-overview"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"non-reference-documentation-writing-the-overview-d248e158","topics":[]},{"title":"Writing the quickstart","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">A quickstart helps new users get through their first experience using software. There are at least two ways to write an API quickstart:<\/p>","href":"topics\/non-reference-quickstart_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-quickstart"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-quickstart-d248e167","topics":[]}]});